    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: MERITOR WABCO WITH "D" VERSION ECU - TROUBLESHOOTING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
            <title>GENERAL MAINTENANCE INFORMATION</title>
            <para>There is no regularly scheduled maintenance required for the Meritor WABCO ABS or ABS/ATC. However,
                ABS does not change current vehicle maintenance requirements.
            </para>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">LAMP CHECK</emph>
                - To make sure the ABS lamp is operating, drivers should check the lamp every time the vehicle is
                started. When the vehicle is started, the ABS lamp should come on momentarily. If it does not come on,
                it could mean a burned-out bulb.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
